4th Annual Investors' Conference on CLOs and Leveraged Loans






































































4th Annual Investors' Conference on CLOs and Leveraged Loans
New York, NY

                                                                        April 21-22, 2015
                                                            






 Description
             Agenda 
             Event Contacts 
             Venue 
             Hotels 
             Sponsors 
            








The conference

            IMN will once again host the premier event for the CLO and leveraged loans sector April 21-22, 2015, in New York City. The 4th Annual Investors' Conference on CLOs and Leveraged Loans program will feature extensive coverage on outlook for issuance in 2015, structural and legal considerations, relative value from a research analyst and investor perspective, the role of CLOs in commercial real estate finance, leveraged loan performance and analysis, ratings methodology for CLOs, and more.Furthermore, this conference provides in depth coverage on the leveraged loan market which is of great interest to the loan level investor. Such discussions include changing lending standards in the loan market, assessing underlying leveraged loan market performance and credit outlook, finding relative value in corporate credit: the loan investor roundtable, the changing face of private lenders, and exploring investment alternatives in the loan market. The conference will serve as a forum for meaningful dialogue to address concerns regarding this dynamic segment of the market.IMN's Investors Conference on CLOs and Leveraged Loans gathers together the best minds in the industry to provide you with thought-leadership on the key challenges and opportunities facing the CLO market.Join the IMN Structured Finance LinkedIn Group for industry and conference updates.
        
Who should attend

CLO ManagersCLO Structurers and BankersLegal and Financial AdvisorsInvestorsCLO Rating AnalystsFinancial Technology ProvidersFinancial Service Providers with an interest in the Leveraged Loan & CLO Market




Tuesday, April 21st, 2015


7:30 AM  Breakfast and Registration 





8:00 AM  Pre- Conference Workshop: Collateralized Loan Obligations, A “101” 


                            This workshop will provide attendees with a strong foundation by explaining the CLO structure, the definition of a leveraged loan, and other key fundamental concepts in the CLO sector.





Vincent Ingato, Senior Portfolio Manager, ZAIS GROUP (Moderator)
Gareth Old, Partner, CLIFFORD CHANCE
Christopher Conrady, Vice President, BNY MELLON
Aleksander Lobanov, Managing Director, DELOITTE & TOUCHE LLP
John Veidis, Director, ZAIS GROUP, LLC




8:45 AM  Hosts' Welcome and Opening Remarks	 





9:00 AM  The CLO Market 2015 Forecast: Mostly Cloudy or Clear Skies Ahead? 


Impact of oil/gas prices on corporate bond performance and ultimately the CLO portfolio performanceOther economic variables: interest rates, liquidityAnticipated regulatory impact of Risk Retention on issuers and investors Investor trends: AAA, mezz, equityPortfolio manager rolesInterim financings/warehousings2.0 deal refinancing outlook





Steven T. Kolyer, Partner, CLIFFORD CHANCE US LLP (Moderator)
