2:00 PM Track B Exploring Alternative Investment Vehicles in the Corporate Credit Market	 


Relative value of alternative products for gaining exposure to corporate credit vs. CLOsTRS, BDCs, CMBS and synthetic tranches (CDX/LCDX)TRS as an alternative means of investor exposure to the loan market vs. direct CLO investmentThe various risk return profiles and tenures that can be achieved in each of the above vehicle alternatives





Joanna Miller-Suna, Counsel, LOWENSTEIN SANDLER LLP (Moderator)
Seema Chetal, Alternative Investments, BANK OF AMERICA MERRILL LYNCH WEALTH MGT
Zaheen Mir, Executive Director, JPMORGAN SECURITIES LLC
Gary Lembo, Director, TENNENBAUM CAPITAL PARTNERS, LLC
Derek Delaney, Managing Director, DMS OFFSHORE INVESTMENT SERVICES




2:50 PM  Refreshment Break 





3:05 PM Track A The Emerging Role of CLO Managers as Direct Lenders	 


Is there a massive shift in lending volume from banks to non banks on the horizon?Niche players to multi strategy asset managersChanges in origination and compensation modelsPrivate to publicly listed vehiclesExploring the growing role of retail funds + BDC's





